{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"Applied the remaining actionable PASS advisories: replaced the novel unread expected_counterexample object with the existing note metadata field; specified direct four-label/non-whitespace assertions for finding_contract; bounded full-run retries to three attempts with 30s/120s waits and a stop/record rule; clarified that kappa is calibrate_criterion expected-vs-observed fire/no-fire agreement, not judge alignment."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784167573492567001,"uuid":"e801d182-02a4-4602-af96-54fcb97b0a5b"}